Young people in particular tend to regard Eatonville as Hurston regarded his entire race: beautiful, problematic and all, neither better nor worse, but also proud, creative, bossy, mad and mixed than other ethnic and racial groups in America.
The voice of Franklin's 18-year-old nephew, Edwin Harvey, is genuine civic affection, and he plans to return to Eatonville after college to work for the local government or the police forces, who need extra strength.
