There was no financial movement either, as the invoices issued were later cancelled, but the agencies avoided mentioning this in their accounts.
The next category of invoice-issuing companies is that of companies directly related to the accused.
Thus, the administrative delegate of the general manager of the company Delta Trió Kft., dealing with the trade in fuel and motor vehicles, whose head office was in Budapest, but where he was not found, was Ivan Kubatov.
