More precisely, the experiment takes place in the following way: an instrument emitting sparks and scattering electroshocks is fixed on the left hand of the experimental subject.
The researchers asked participants in the experiment to look sustainedly at two paintings, one being the Virgin Mary painted by Sassoferrato in the 17th century and the other, the Lady with the Hermine painted by Leonardo da Vinci in the 15th century.
