Open Office is the third edition of the "anti-Microsoft" package
Today is the release day of OpenOffice.org.3.0, the open source suite of personal productivity that aims to reach more and more users, from home to office, from professionals to the public administration, offering a free alternative to the most famous Microsoft Office.
Following a work of almost a year, carried out by volunteer developers, supervised by SUN Microsystem, the new Open Office package is shown to the general public with various novelties: from the welcome screen, and the interface revised and become less austere, to others more important, such as the compatibility born for the latest operating system Apple Mac OS X.
Open Office has paid particular attention to the interaction with the Office 2007 suite, and it is indeed possible to open documents with the new Microsoft extension (.docx, .xlsx, .pptx.)
Also interesting, some functions specific to some modules, such as the one that allows to reduce the dimensions of PowerPoint presentations, useful for example, to send them by email, or to import PDF files in the graphic development module, retaining the original appearance of the page.
Always on this front, it is possible to create "hybrid PDF" documents that join the typical graphic of the Adobe format with the elements of a spreadsheet or a word processor.
Collaboration between several people is an element that has had various improvements within the applications: in the spreadsheet, various users can intervene, avoiding conflicts on changes, in the elaboration of texts, because each collaborator is assigned a color of comments for better recognition in the revision phase.
Some companies are even working to bring some OpenOffice features to the web (on the cloud, on the cloud), and in the coming weeks, they should issue the definitive result.
The Italian version can be downloaded at http://en.openoffice.org/download/3.0.0/download300.html and is in addition to the English version that has been on the mirror since Friday.
In addition to Windows and Mac OS, the suite is as usual available in addition, for the Linux operating system.
On request, the installation cd can be shipped home or to the workplace.
And if the theme of free can be a means to spread it in homes, it is precisely in the business, that the Open Office suite tries the great challenge, can already count on various projects carried out in the public administration and schools.
Not to mention the realities that offer a training, consultation and assistance service, ideal for small and medium-sized companies, which could also open up to business prospects.
Open Office consists of five main modules: Writer, for the equivalent video writing of Word; Calc, is the spreadsheet that aims to replace Excel; Impress, for rival PowerPoint presentations; Dbase, such as the famous Access, is the program that allows you to work on databases; finally Drwa is the graphical module.
Target for 2008, reach 5 million downloads, and considering that today there are almost 3 million and 600 miles, it is likely that with the release of the new version, we can even exceed the expected figure
